Sentencas: A multivariable hybrid experimental model of a solid oxide fuel cell stack is developed in this paper.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack

Sentencas: The model consists of an improved radial basis function (RBF) neural network model and a pressure-incremental model.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack

Sentencas: The improved RBF model is built to predict the stack voltage with different temperatures and current density.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack

Sentencas: Likewise, the pressure-incremental model is constructed to predict the stack voltage under various hydrogen, oxygen, and water partial pressures.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack

Sentencas: We combine the two models together and make a powerful hybrid multivariable model that can predict the voltage under any current density, temperature, hydrogen, oxygen, and water partial pressure.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack

Sentencas: The validity and accuracy of modeling are tested by simulations, and the simulation results show that it is feasible to build the hybrid multivariable experimental model.
Titulo: A Hybrid Experimental Model of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack
